getNodeIds

public java.lang.String getNodeIds()
                            throws VINException
FIXME: to remove when node attributes can be used. This method is to workaround the fact that we cannot put node attributes in dvt:diagram. We instead send a diagram attribute containing all the java nodeIds in the same order than the set of nodes. We then assume that dvt:diagram will use this order for its getNodeByIndex() method. With this assumption, a map can be constructed between Java and Dvt node ids.

Returns:
A String containing Java node ids separated by spaces, in the same order as the one the nodes themeselves are sent
Throws:
VINException

getNodeIdsWithMoreOverlays

public java.lang.String getNodeIdsWithMoreOverlays()
                                            throws VINException
FIXME: to remove when node attributes can be used. This method is to workaround the fact that we cannot put node attributes in dvt:diagram. To ensure vertical links reaches the the correct part of nodes, we need this method to provide information to the layout on which nodes have an overlay.

Returns:
A String containing Java node ids of nodes with overlays, separated by spaces.
Throws:
VINException

setLevelOfDetails

public boolean setLevelOfDetails(java.lang.String focusNodeId)
                          throws VINException
Traverse the model and determines the level of detail for all nodes and links. Node.levelOfDetail is updated for all nodes. Link.levelOfDetail is updated for all links.

Parameters:
focusNodeId - [in]: the node id for the focus node.
Returns:
true if "large data set mode" is required (total number of nodes > MAX_NODES_DETAIL_HIGH) if false is returned all nodes are in HIGH detail.
Throws:
VINException
